                   Anonymous FTP Sites List (2003-11-02)

     This document contains a list of currently known anonymous FTP
     sites. It is updated roughly on a monthly basis. The newest version
     is located at http://www.ftp-sites.org/. This FTP sites list can be
     distributed freely as long as the above mentioned link (or just the
     URL depending on the format) remains included. The data needed to
     build this FTP sites list has been obtained from the file search
     engine FileWatcher.org. The list is far from being complete. You
     can report missing anonymous FTP sites or other suggestions
     regarding this list to Oliver Maruhn <ftpsearch@filewatcher.org>.
     This list of anonymous FTP sites has been inspired by Perry Rovers'
     FTP sites list which has been actively maintained till 1997. Please
     read his FTP FAQ if you want to learn more about FTP.

     Version: 2003-11-02

     +-----------------------------------------------------------------+
     | Quick Reference:                                                |
     | ac, ai, ar, at, au, be, bg, br, by, ca, cc, ch, cl, cn, com,    |
     | cr, cx, cz, de, dk, edu, ee, es, fi, fr, ge, gov, gr, hk, hr,   |
     | hu, id, ie, il, in, info, int, is, it, jp, kg, kr, kz, lt, lu,  |
     | lv, mil, mx, my, net, ni, nl, no, nu, nz, org, pl, pt, ro, ru,  |
     | sa, se, sg, si, sk, su, th, tk, tr, tv, tw, ua, uk, us, ve, ws, |
     | yu, za                                                          |
     +-----------------------------------------------------------------+

Latest Version

       * Primary site: http://www.ftp-sites.org/
       * Mirror site:
         http://blubb.at/ftp-list/anonymous_ftp_sites_list.html (hosted
         by blubb.at)

     Please send an email if you want to mirror the Anonymous FTP Sites
     List.

Other Formats

       * Package of all HTML pages (compressed):

            * anonymous_ftp_sites_list_html.tar.bz2
            * anonymous_ftp_sites_list_html.tar.gz
            * anonymous_ftp_sites_list_html.zip

       * Single plain text file (compressed):

            * anonymous_ftp_sites_list.txt.bz2
            * anonymous_ftp_sites_list.txt.gz
            * anonymous_ftp_sites_list_txt.zip

       * PDF file:

            * anonymous_ftp_sites_list.pdf

       * Number of anonymous FTP sites: 5,593
          
       * Total file number on all anonymous FTP sites: 259,497,808

 please report them via e-mail to <system@ai.univie.ac.at>.

 messages that may be confusing your ftp client.

 If you don't like this policy, disconnect now!

  of /outgoing directory. /outgoing directory is structured by project
  acronyms. Some files are also in /pub directory.
     Files are uploadable into one of /incoming subdirectories, which
  again correspond to the IIASA research project acronyms. Please note
  that uploaded files are not DOWNLOADABLE !

 myrtle.services.adelaide.edu.au FTP server (Version wu-2.6.1(2) Fri Nov 30 10:22:51
 CST 2001) ready.
 Welcome to the Anonymous FTP Service at the University of Adelaide.

 This server is located at the North Terrace campus of the University of
 Adelaide, South Australia.

 You can search through a list of available files via the following command
   quote site exec index PATTERN
 where PATTERN is a regular expression suitable for grep.

 The server will also perform (de)compression on the fly using either gzip
 or standard Unix compress. To use this facility to fetch a file just add,
 or remove, the appropriate suffix (.gz for GNU zip and .Z for compress).

 If your FTP client crashes or hangs shortly after login please try using
 a dash (-) as the first character of your password. This will turn off the
 informational messages that may be confusing your FTP client.

 Access to this service is permitted at anytime but performance may be
 superior outside of normal office hours (ie 9am 'til 5pm weekdays).

 All transfers to and from this service are logged. If you don't like this
 then disconnect now!

 Any queries about this service should be directed to ftp@adelaide.edu.au.

         this off, start your password with "-". This include the FTP client

       * Welcome message:

 fas.sfu.ca FTP server (Version wu-2.6.2(1) Fri Nov 30 12:04:39 PST 2001) ready.

         The ftp pub directory is broken down into departments. These
 departments are further broken down to lab/groups.  The lab/groups
 directory is created by "gripe@css.sfu.ca", if it does not exist already,
 and the ownership will be set to a representative of that lab/group.  It
 will be up to the representative of the lab/group to install the files
 in their appropriate directory.  To install the files:

          cp <files> to  /fas-info/ftp/pub/<cs eg.>/<lab/group directory>

 Please note that compressed files can be uncompressed before transmitting
 by removing the postfix ".Z" or ".gz" from the name of the file.


 User ftp logged in.  Access restrictions apply.

  ---------- ---------- ---------- ---------- ---------- ---------- ----------
  University of Alberta    FTP and Information Server
 
  If you have files that are of global interest to our University
  Community, you are welcome to submit them to this server.
 
 
  This CNS Information Server is maintained by
 
         ftpmaster@ftp.srv.ualberta.ca
 
  Problems?  CNS Help Desk
       helpdesk@ualberta.ca          (780) 492-9400
 
  Some ftp clients are confused by continuation messages. Try using a
  dash (-) as the first character of your password.
 
 
  ---------- ---------- ---------- ---------- ---------- ---------- ----------
  EXTENSIONS:
 
  What do all those crazy file extensions mean?
  Well, here is the answer.
 
  .TXT   The file is a document, rather than a program. Just plain ASCII text.
         No de-compression is needed.
 
  .ZIP   An MS-DOS format. Use the PKZIP package, which will bundle up a truckload
         of files, into one adding a .ZIP at the end.
 
  .ARC   A DOS format that requires the use of ARC or ARCE.
 
  .hqx   A Macintosh format that needs BinHex for de-compression.
 
  .sit   A Macintosh format, requires Stuffit.
 
  .tar   Tar saves and restores multiple UNIX files into one big UNIX file
 
  .shar  A Unix format. Use Unshar
 
  .gz   The file is Gzipped with the GNU utility gzip.  Requires gunzip.
 
  .Z    This is a Unix compression method.  Requires uncompress.
 
  .ZOO  A Unix and MS-DOS format. Requires the use of a program called zoo.
 
  .ps   PostScript files generated by drawing and publishing packages.
 
  .dvi  Files produced by processing TeX and LaTeX source files.
  ---------- ---------- ---------- ---------- ---------- ---------- ----------

  Guest login ok, access restrictions apply.
  Local time is: Fri Aug 29 03:37:28 2003

 ***************************************************************************D
 *    Welcome to the Computer Associates International, Inc. FTP server     *
 ****************************************************************************
 *               This is a DOWNLOAD-ONLY FTP Server                         *
 ****************************************************************************
 This FTP server provides access to patches for many CA products.

 These files are zipped using cazip or other common zip utilities.  You can
 find cazip at /caproducts/Cazipxp.exe

 There are 3 FTP areas as listed below:

 /caproducts - This is a public area of patches - organized by product
        directories.  /pub and /CAproducts directories are the same as
        /caproducts. No user id or password is required to access this area.

 /priv - This is a private area of patches available to clients who have been
        given a user id and password by CA Technical Support (limited
        distribution).

 /outgoing - This is a private area used by CA Technical Support to provide
        files to clients who are working with CA on new issues.

 For additional support information, please visit the CA technical support
 web site at:     http://support.ca.com

       * Total file size: 3.20 MB
       * System: UNIX Type: L8
       * Welcome message:

 jwwalker.com NcFTPd Server (licensed copy) ready.
 You are user #2 of 32 simultaneous users allowed.

 Welcome to the FTP archive at Jim Walker's Software Source.

 Most files here are compressed with StuffIt and encoded in
 MacBinary format.  In some cases, your FTP client or web
 browser may decode and decompress the files with no help
 from you.  If that doesn't happen, all you should have to
 do is drop the file on StuffIt Expander.

 If StuffIt Expander tells you that the file is corrupt,
 you are probably seeing a bug in some versions of the
 StuffIt Engine.  Try this: Remove the StuffIt Engine and
 StuffIt Engine PowerPlug from your Extensions folder and
 then drag and drop the .bin file onto the StuffIt Expander
 icon. You do not need to restart the machine to do this,
 and when you are done you can simply put the Engine and
 PowerPlug back in the Extensions folder.

 Logged in anonymously.

 Compression Formats:
 -------------------
 .hqx files are compressed using Binhex Mac and PC utilities.
 .zip files are compressed using PKZip version 2.04g PC Utility.

  Accounts are available via telnet shell.Theworld.com, or via direct-dial by
  calling 617-739-9753: 8N1, X2/V.90 (56K) V.34+ (33.6kbps), V.34 (28.8kbps),
  etc. or via our web page: http://www.TheWorld.com.

  (excluding AK+HI.)

 aware of material on its network or system that infringes the
 exclusive copyright rights of one or more IDSA members.  This notice is
 addressed to you as the agent designated by xxx
 to receive notifications of claimed infringement, as so reflected in the
 current records of the U.S. Copyright Office.  Under penalty of perjury, we
 hereby affirm that the IDSA is authorized to act on behalf of the IDSA members
 whose exclusive copyright rights we believe to be infringed as described
 herein.

 IDSA has a good faith belief that the Internet site found at
 http://www.stormaster.com/ infringes the rights of one or more IDSA members by
 offering for download one or more unauthorized copies of one or more game
 products protected by copyright, including, but not limited to:

 Dig Dug
 Donkey Kong
 Frogger
 Mario
 Pac Man
 SWAT
 Tron 2.0 (game)

 The unauthorized copies of such game product[s] appearing on, or made available
 through, such site are listed and/or identified on such Internet site by their
 titles, variations thereof or depictions of associated artwork (any such game
 titles, copies, listings and/or other depictions of, or references to, any
 contents of such game product, are hereinafter referred to as
 "Infringing Material").  Based on the information at its
 disposal on 4/27/2003 7:18:34 AM GMT, IDSA believes that the statements in this
 notice are accurate and correctly describe the infringing nature and status of
 the Infringing Material.

 Accordingly, IDSA hereby requests xxx to
 immediately remove or disable access to the Infringing Material at the URL
 address identified above.

 Should you have questions, please contact the IDSA at the above listed mailing
 address or by replying to this email.  Please also include the above noted
 Reference Number in the subject line of all email correspondence.

 We thank you for your cooperation in this matter.  Your prompt response is
 appreciated.

 Regards,

 Robert L. Hunter, IV
 Interactive Digital Software Association

 r4h Microsoft FTP Service (Version 5.0).
 Welcome to the FTP session
          Please Note

 * After logging in as Site Administrator, you're inside your ftproot directory
 \Inetpub\ftproot. You have access to the following directories:

   home: which points to \home, your home directory.
   log : which points to \LogFiles, it contains the web/ftp raw log data.
   wwwroot: which points to \Inetpub\wwwroot , it contains your published content
 for the Web Site.
   anonymous: which can be accessed by anonymous users. If you have anonymous FTP
 enabled, you can put content here for anonymous users to download from.

 * If Anonymous FTP is enabled for the Site, anonymous users can download files from
 their ftproot. The ftproot for anonymous users is: \InetPub\ftproot\anonymous.
 * If Anonymous FTP is disabled for a Site, only the Site Administrator can ftp to
 the Site with his web Control Panel username/password.
 * For more information, please see online help.

 htrp-d10 FTP server (Version wu-2.4(31) Mon Nov 19 11:23:49 EST 2001) ready.
 Welcome to our AOL Members' FTP/WWW Site!

 This site is made available for internet users to exchange
 files via FTP and access user web pages.  Each AOL user has
 a disk quota of 2Mb; please respect this limit on uploads.
     
 You must "cd" to the AOL user's screen name to access their
 data.  There is no casual browsing of user archives.

 The AOL FTP GUI requires you specify the initial directory
 (AOL username) after the "Other Site" name, eg.
     members:/username
 if you do not wish to be placed in your own directory.  The
 alias "users" may also be used in place of "members".

 Please read the "/usersFAQ.txt" document for answers to some
 frequently asked questions about using this site.

 All transfers are logged.  FTP questions or problem reports
 should be sent via e-mail to "ftpmaster@aol.com".

 Please Note: The members.aol.com servers will be rebooted on
 Sunday mornings at 05:00EST (10:00GMT).

 Thank-you for choosing AOL!

 moops.anphy.uni-duesseldorf.de FTP server ready.
 Herzlich Willkommen, FTP-Benutzer!

 Dies ist zwar kein experimenteller, sondern ein angewandter FTP-Server, aber
 trotzdem ist das Angebot nur klein.
 Enthalten sind:
         1. Software fuer die Vorlesung "Computersimulationen physikalischer
                 und technischer Systeme
         2. Die aktuelle Beta-Version von gnuplot (momentan pre-3.6 pl 328)
         4. Je nach aktuellem Plattenplatz diverser Schnickschnack.
         5. Ein NFS-Mount des FTP-Servers des RZ (pub/duesseldorf)

 Dieser Server unterstuetzt das automatische Entpacken von *.gz-Archiven
 sowie das automatische Erstellen von *.tar.gz-Archiven; haengen Sie an den
 Verzeichnisnamen einfach die Endung .tar.gz an bzw. lassen Sie .gz weg.

 ftpadmin@schulzeundschultze.anphy.uni-duesseldorf.de.

============================== ftp://ftp.dante.de/

       * Total file number: 81,958
       * Total file size: 6.10 GB
       * System: UNIX Type: L8
       * Directories in /pub/: fptex/, tex/
       * Mirror directories: experimental/
       * Welcome message:

 nova.dante.de FTP server (Version wu-2.6.2(3) Mon Aug 11 11:10:16 CEST 2003) ready.
 Willkommen! Dies ist der ftp-Server fuer das Archiv von DANTE e.V.
 Bei ungewoehnlichen Problemen senden Sie bitte eine email an:

     ftpmaint@dante.de

 Fuer ftp-Klienten, die mit mehrzeiligen Antworten nicht zurecht kommen,
 bietet es sich an, als erstes Zeichen des Kennwortes ein Minuszeichen (-)
 einzugeben -- dadurch werden alle Antworten auf eine Zeile begrenzt.

 Dies ist der de-Knoten des Comprehensive TeX Archive Network (CTAN). Andere
 Server im CTAN und die entsprechenden Verzeichnisse sind:

         ftp.tex.ac.uk           /tex-archive  (England)
         ctan.tug.org         /tex-archive  (USA)

 Um das Internet nicht unnoetig zu belasten, sollte der naechstgelegene
 Server oder CTAN-Spiegel benutzt werden.  Eine Liste der CTAN-Spiegel
 steht in /tex-archive/CTAN.sites.

 WICHTIGER HINWEIS:

 Dieser ftp-Server erlaubt das dynamische Erstellen von zip-, zoo-, tar-,
 tar.Z- oder tar.gz-Archiven. Wenn Sie ein ganzes Verzeichnis holen moechten,
 so gehen Sie ein Verzeichnis zurueck und haengen beim ,get' an den Namen
 des Verzeichnisses .zip, .zoo, .tar, .tar.Z oder .tar.gz an. So wird z.B.
 durch

    cd /tex-archive/macros/latex
    binary
    get base.zip

 das gesamte base-Verzeichnis als .zip-Datei gepackt und transferiert.


                       Suche nach bestimmten Dateien

 Sie koennen das Inhaltsverzeichnis des Archivs nach Dateinamen durchsuchen,
 indem Sie

   quote site index string

 eingeben, wobei "string" Ihr Suchstring ist. Beachten Sie, dass dies dann
 NICHT funktioniert, wenn Sie ein `-' als erstes Zeichen Ihres Passwortes
 eingegeben haben.

 ftp.fh-muenchen.de NcFTPd Server (free educational license) ready.
 You are user #1 of 50 simultaneous users allowed.

 -------------------------------------
 Welcome to the FH-Muenchen FTP-Server
 -------------------------------------
 Please note: the FH-Muenchen is not running a usual ftp server.
 There are a lot of good ftp-servers nearby. You may try for example:
   ftp.leo.org         ftp.lrz-muenchen.de
 On this server ftp.fh-muenchen.de there are only a few programs kept
 that are of particular interest to the Fachhochschule Muenchen
 (University of Applied Sciences).
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
 Bitte beachten Sie: die Fachhochschule Muenchen betreibt keinen
 FTP-Server im ueblichen Sinne. Es gibt mehrere gut gepflegte FTP-Server
 in unmittelbarer "Netz-Nachbarschaft". Unsere Empfehlungen:
   ftp.leo.org         ftp.lrz-muenchen.de
 Auf dem Server ftp.fh-muenchen.de werden nur wenige Programme gespeichert,
 die fuer die FH Muenchen von besonderem Interesse sind.
 Rechenzentrum der FHM, Hartmut Hotzel, Hotzel@mailserv.rz.fh-muenchen.de
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
 .

 Logged in anonymously.

 Welcome to the anonymous FTP service of the University of Hamburg.
 This host is the FTP server of the Department of Computer Science.

 If your FTP client crashes or hangs shortly after login, try using a
 dash (-) as the first character of your password. This will turn off
 the (sometimes important ... :-) informational messages which may be
 confusing your ftp client.

 Files with the suffix '.gz' or '.z' are compressed with GNU gzip.
 You'll find sources for gzip and gunzip in pub/soft/gnu/gzip-1.2.4.tar

 To search for a file of a given name in the complete archive listing use:

   quote site index string

 where "string" is your search string. Note that this will NOT work if you
 entered a `-' as the first character of your password.

 Send mail concerning the archive and the incoming directory to
 ftpmaint@informatik.uni-hamburg.de

 Please try to retrieve things outside of normal business hours only,
 ie 0900-1800 MET.  The local time is Fri Aug 29 11:37:06 2003.

  PROBLEMS:

  to ftpadm@informatik.uni-stuttgart.de.

  INCOMING:
  You can upload files to the in.coming directory. Please send e-mail
  to ftpadm@informatik.uni-stuttgart.de describing what you have uploaded.
  Uploads without such mail will be deleted.

  DOWNLOAD:
  You can compress/gzip files:       You can uncompress/gunzip files:
     FILE <filename>:                   FILE <filename>.Z or <filename>.gz:
     get <filename>.Z                   get <filename>
     get <filename>.gz

  You can tar+compress/gzip directories:
     get <dirname>.tar
     get <dirname>.tar.Z
     get <dirname>.tar.gz

 If you don't like this policy, disconnect NOW!

 If your FTP client crashes or hangs shortly after login, try using a
 dash (-) as the first character of your password.  This will turn off
 the informational messages which may be confusing your FTP client.

 "get" <directory>.<suffix> or <file>.<suffix> where suffix comes from
 the set [gz, Z, tar, tar.Z, tar.gz] will compress and/or tar a file or
 directory for you on the fly.  Likewise if you strip suffixes from
 filenames, they can be uncompressed.  And we support the "reget" command.

 Contact ftp@ips.cs.tu-bs.de (FTP Administration) for any questions.

 aragon.math.uni-rostock.de FTP server (Version wu-2.6.2(1) Tue Dec 4 19:48:58 MET
 2001) ready.
 ===============================================================================
  >>>    You are connected to   ftp.math.uni-rostock.de
  >>>                          Department of Mathematics
  >>>                            University of Rostock

         This anonymous FTP site is in Rostock, Germany, Europe.
         It's Fri Aug 29 13:50:41 2003
         Please mail questions, comments etc. to
                  webmaster.mathematik@mathematik.uni-rostock.de

         Preprints are under /pub/preprint/
         RoMaKo Articles are under /pub/romako/
         Staff home directories are under /pub/members/
         FakeCD is under /pub/tools/
         Upload directory is /pub/members/incoming
         (Please note that you don't have read permissions there.)

  This site allows dynamic compression/decompression and creation of
  .tar.Z, tar.gz and .zip files.
  If you want to get a preprint uncompressed, leave out the .Z suffix.
  Do something like

    cd /pub/preprint/1997
    get pre97_17.ps

  This will uncompress the preprint on the fly and transfer the
  PostScript(tm) Source.

  If you want to get a whole directory, do something like

    cd /pub
    get tools.zip          (or tools.tar.gz or tools.tar.Z)

  This will compress the whole tools/ directory on the fly and
  transfer it as .zip (or tar.gz or tar.Z) file.

  Welcome, unknown@pD9E418EB.dip.t-dialin.net,
  you are # 1 of 16 possible users.
 ===============================================================================

 data on this system that you could get elsewhere.

 It's now Fri Aug 29 13:02:51 2003 , good times are 10:00-18:00.

 You are user 1 of a current maximum of 10 user(s). If you're connecting
 from outside the swb.de domain, you'll be much safer by using FSP (port 21)
 instead.  Do not block more then one FTP session, this behavior is frowned
 upon and offenders will be blacklisted.

 If you use anonymous access, provide a valid mail address or user id
 on your machine (at least in the form "username@").

 In the case you use a WWW browser like Mosaic or Netscape to access
 this FTP server, please consider using a nice FTP tool like ncftp
 instead. WWW browsers put a serious strain on the machine due to
 them constantly reconnecting for every request.

 Welcome, archive user!  This is an FTP server for the University of
 Mainz, Germany. If you have any unusual problems, please report them
 via e-mail to

     ftpadmin@mail.uni-mainz.de

 Access is allowed all day.

 All transfers are logged with your host name and email address.
 If you don't like this policy, disconnect now!

 If you do have problems, please try using a dash (-) as the first
 character of your password -- this will turn off the continuation
 messages that may be confusing your ftp client.

 IMPORTANT NOTE:

 This ftp server supports dynamic creation of zip, tar, tar.Z or
 tar.gz archives. If you want the contents of a directory (*and all its
 subdirectories*), go to the level above and `get' the directory name
 suffixed by .zip, tar, tar.Z or tar.gz.

 To obtain a listing of a zip-, tar-, tar.Z- oder tar.gz archive
 file you may append the suffix -lst to the filename, e.g.

 get /pub/gnu/oleo/oleo-1.6.tar.gz-lst

  Welcome to the anonymous ftp server hosted by UNC-Chapel Hill

  local space for uploads.  Any attempt to upload information

 the set [gz, Z, tar, tar.Z, tar.gz] will compress and/or tar a file or
 directory for you on the fly.  Likewise if you strip suffixes from
 filenames, they can be uncompressed for you.

  Access is allowed 24 hours a day.

  the multi-line messages that may be causing your difficulties.

  Files owned by "ftp" (i.e., placed here by anonymous ftp) will be
  deleted after 7 days unless other arrangements have been made.
  Large files that are not compressed will be compressed nightly.

  This ftp server supports automatic tar and compress features
  when retrieving files.  See /info/ftp.server.extensions for details.

 Welcome to the CMU Computer Club FTP service
 Welcome to ftp.club.cc.cmu.edu [phosphorus.club.cc.cmu.edu, 128.2.4.171], a
 service of the Carnegie Mellon Computer Club. We are currently carrying
 kernel.org and gnu.org, updated every 6 hours via rsync.

 This machine is a Pentium II/333 running Debian GNU/Linux 3.0. Files are stored
 on AFS (http://www.openafs.org/) fileservers, which are 433MHz DEC Alpha
 workstations, also running Debian 3.0.

 Requests for additional mirrors will be considered on the basis of relevance
 and available disk space. Send mail to gripe@club.cc.cmu.edu.  Monetary and/or
 hardware contributions are welcome; send us mail if you would like to
 make a contribution!

 This archive is also available on the web at http://www.club.cc.cmu.edu/pub
 If you have an AFS client (see http://www.openafs.org/), you can access it
 directly from your filesystem in /afs/club.cc.cmu.edu/archive

 Some software on this site supports encryption. Please read the file
 README.encrypt before downloading any software.

 anon.cs.rochester.edu FTP server (Version wu-2.6.1(1) Tue Nov 28 10:15:20 EST 2000)
 ready.
 Welcome, archive user!  This is an experimental FTP server.  If have any
 unusual problems, please report them via e-mail to root@anon.cs.rochester.edu
 If you do have problems, please try using a dash (-) as the first character
 of your password -- this will turn off the continuation messages that may
 be confusing your ftp client.

 This server can transparently compress and uncompress files and
 generate tar archives of directories:

   True Filename  Specified Filename   Action before transmitting file:
   -------------  -------------------  ----------------------------------
   <filename>     <filename>.Z         Compress file using Unix compress
   <filename>     <filename>.gz        Compress file using GNU Zip
   <filename>.Z   <filename>           Uncompress file
   <filename>.gz  <filename>           Un-gnuzip file
   <directory>    <directory>.tar      Tar directory
   <directory>    <directory>.tar.Z    Tar and compress directory
   <directory>    <directory>.tar.gz   Tar and GNU Zip directory

   Note: GNU Zip (gzip) does better compression than compress.

 Please read the file pub/README for an overview of our public filesystem.

 Guest login ok, access restrictions apply.

 Department of Computer Science and Engineering, UC San Diego

 Files available for anonymous FTP are in /pub.  If you can't find what
 you are looking for on this machine, try ucsd.edu (132.239.1.1).

 All transfers are logged with your hostname and e-mail address.

 This ftp server supports on-the-fly compression, uncompression and tar.

 If your ftp client has problems with the extended messages (or if you
 simply find such messages annoying), connect again and use a password
 that begins with "-" to disable these messages.

 For further assistance, send e-mail to csehelp@cs.ucsd.edu

 ftp1.cs.wisc.edu FTP server (Version wu-2.6.1(3) Tue Aug 19 11:16:55 CDT 2003)
 ready.
  Welcome, archive user!  This is an experimental FTP server.  If you
  have any unusual problems, please report them via electronic mail to
  mirror@cs.wisc.edu.
 
  If you do have problems, please try using a dash (-) as the first
  character of your password -- this will turn off the continuation
  messages that may be confusing your ftp client.
 
  There are some extensions to the FTP server such that if you
  specify a filename (when using a RETRIEVE command) such that:
 
  True Filename Specified Filename  Action before transmitting file:
  ------------- ------------------- ----------------------------------
  <filename>.Z  <filename>          Uncompress file
  <filename>.gz <filename>          Un-gnuzip file
  <filename>.z  <filename>          Un-gnuzip file
  <filename>    <filename>.Z        Compress file
  <filename>    <filename>.gz       Gnu Zip file
  <filename>    <filename>.z        Gnu Zip file
  <directory>   <directory>.tar     Tar directory
  <filename>    <filename>.tar.Z    Tar and compress directory
  <filename>    <filename>.tar.gz   Tar and Gnu Zip directory
  ====================================================================
  Note: Gnu Zip (gzip) does better compression than compress

 Guest login ok, access restrictions apply.

 the set [gz, Z, tar, tar.Z, tar.gz] will compress and/or tar a file or
 directory for you on the fly.  Likewise if you strip suffixes from
 filenames, they can be uncompressed for you.

 lion.icpsr.umich.edu FTP server (Version wu-2.6.2(2) Sun Jul 14 17:58:11 EDT 2002)
 ready.
 Access to these data sets and documentation for them is
 provided as a service of the  Inter-university Consortium
 for Political and Social Research (ICPSR) and the research
 projects that generate the data.  ICPSR is a consortium of
 member colleges and universities, united to facilitate
 social science research and education.  For over 30 years, ICPSR
 has served social scientists around the world by providing:

 * A central  repository and dissemination service for machine-readable
 social science data
 * Training facilities in basic and advanced techniques of quantitative
 social analysis
 * Resources that facilitate the use of advanced computer technology by
 social scientists

 ICPSR provides facilities and services for an international community
 of scholars that no one college or university could offer independently. 

 Further information about ICPSR can be obtained from the ICPSR World Wide
 Web home page:
      www.icpsr.umich.edu

 If you are interested in full access to the resources and
 services of ICPSR for your institution, please contact
      Executive Director
      ICPSR
      PO Box 1248
      Ann Arbor, MI 48106

 hurricane FTP server (Version wu-2.6.2(1) Fri Dec 7 14:56:43 MST 2001) ready.
 This is the UCAR Joint Office for Science Support (JOSS) FTP server.

 You are connected to a United States Government computer.  Use of
 this computer for unauthorized purposes is a violation of federal law
 (reference: Public Law 99-474).  Any activity on this computer may be
 logged and monitored.  By remaining connected to this computer and using
 its services, you are consenting to such logging and monitoring.

 This FTP server is intended to provide a repository for data flowing into
 and out of JOSS.  Any other use must be authorized by JOSS on a case by
 case basis.

 Incoming FTP is located in subdirectories of /pub/incoming.  You *must*
 know the name of the subdirectory in which you wish to deposit data, and
 you *must* change to that directory in a single step.  /pub/incoming itself
 is unreadable for security reasons.  This makes some FTP clients, such as
 those popular on Windows, believe that there are no subdirectories.  If
 this is the case, please check your software for a command to change
 directories in a single step.

 Please contact sysadmin@joss.ucar.edu if you have difficulty with this FTP
 server.

 ftp.MATH.ORST.EDU FTP server (Version wu-2.6.2(5) Sun Jul 6 16:56:34 PDT 2003)
 ready.
       Welcome to the OSU math department anonymous ftp archive.

 You can retrieve an entire directory subtree as a tar file or
 compressed tar file by simply appending .tar or .tar.Z or .tar.gz to
 the name of a directory, as  "get dirname.tar",  "get dirname.tar.Z"
 or "get dirname.tar.gz".
 Note that it is necessary to be in binary mode, and perhaps it is a good
 idea to check whether the contents of the subtree are already compressed...

 Please do not waste your time or mine by attempting to use the "incoming"
 directories as "warez" repositories.  Contents cannot be listed or
 retrieved, with the same holding for the one permitted level of subdirectory.
 Uploads into "incoming" directories are logged and monitored.

 Prepend a dash (-) to your initial ftp login password to turn off
 blabber like this if your ftp client is choking.
   Please report any problems via e-mail to ftp-bugs@math.orst.edu

 sonia.math.sunysb.edu FTP server (Version wu-2.4.2-academ[BETA-18-VR14](1) Thu Feb
 25 14:07:16 EST 1999) ready.
   This is an experimental FTP server.  If your FTP client crashes or
   hangs shortly after login please try using a dash (-) as the first
   character of your password.  This will turn off the informational
   messages that may be confusing your FTP client.

   This FTP server has several extensions.  In particular, files may be
   compressed or uncompressed, and/or tarred at transmission  time.

  True Filename  Specified Filename   Action
  -------------- -------------------- ---------------------------------------
  <filename>.Z   <filename>           Decompress file before transmitting
  <filename>     <filename>.Z         Compress <filename> before transmitting
  <filename>     <filename>.tar       Tar <filename> before transmitting
  <filename>     <filename>.tar.Z     Tar and compress <filename> before
                                         transmitting

   If you have questions or comments about this FTP server, send electronic
   mail to the address "help@math.sunysb.edu".

 ftp.math.utah.edu FTP server (Version wu-2.6.2(1) Mon Dec 3 13:07:13 MST 2001)
 ready.
 ************************************************************************
 * This is an experimental FTP server.  If your FTP client crashes or   *
 * hangs shortly after login please try using a dash (-) as the first   *
 * character of your password.  This will turn off the informational    *
 * messages that may be confusing your FTP client.                      *
 *                                                                      *
 * This system may be used 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.  The local    *
 * time in Salt Lake City, Utah, USA, is Sun Nov  2 00:45:51 2003.      *
 *                                                                      *
 * Support for dynamic compression and decompression, listing of archive*
 * files, and creation of archive files for directory subtrees, is      *
 * available.  Get the file /README.archive-features for details.       *
 *                                                                      *
 * The ftp "QUOTE SITE INDEX pattern" command be be used to search for  *
 * filenames in a master index; get /README.site-commands for details.  *
 *                                                                      *
 * Files can be deposited in /incoming, subject to restrictions given   *
 * in /README.uploads.                                                  *
 *                                                                      *
 * cd shorthands: bib: (/pub/tex/bib), bibnet: (/pub/tex/bibnet),       *
 * dvi: (/pub/tex/dvi), s: /pub/bibnet/subjects)                        *
 *                                                                      *
 * Report any problems by e-mail to ftp-problems@math.utah.edu.             *
 *                                                                      *
 * You are user 9 of a maximum of 50.                                  *
 *                                                                      *
 * MD5SUM files contain MD5 checksums of archive files.  The companion  *
 * MD5SUM.asc file is digitally-signed by PGP (Pretty Good Privacy).    *
 * Verify the authenticity of the latter with "pgp MD5SUM.asc", and     *
 * then use md5sum (part of the GNU textutils and coreutils packages,   *
 * ftp://ftp.gnu.org/pub/gnu) to compute the checksum of any downloaded *
 * file, and compare with the value in the MD5SUM copy from pgp.        *
 ************************************************************************

   it was last modified on Wed Jun 18 10:56:34 2003 - 137 days ago
 Please read the file README.archive-features
   it was last modified on Wed Jun 18 11:00:17 2003 - 137 days ago

 ------------------------------------------------------------------------

 The following conversions are available:

 Listed filename     Specified filename   Action
 file.{Z,z,gz}       file                 uncompress
 file                file.Z               compress
 file                file.{z,gz}          gzip
 file                file.tar             tar
 file                file.tar.{Z}         tar and compress
 file                file.tar.{z,gz}      tar and gzip
 file.gz             file.Z               ungzip and compress

 net.tamu.edu FTP server (Version wu-2.6.1(2) Tue Nov 7 10:22:10 CST 2000) ready.
 This system is for the use of authorized users only.
 Individuals using this computer system without authority, or in
 excess of their authority, are subject to having all of their
 activities on this system monitored and recorded by system
 personnel.

 system, or in the course of system maintenance, the activities
 of authorized users may also be monitored.

 Anyone using this system expressly consents to such monitoring
 and is advised that if such monitoring reveals possible
 evidence of criminal activity, system personnel may provide the
 evidence of such monitoring to law enforcement officials.

 do not agree with this policy, then you should disconnect
 immediately.

 shekel.mcl.cs.columbia.edu FTP server (Version wu-2.6.0(3) Tue Oct 19 18:30:07 EDT
 1999) ready.
                      WELCOME TO FTP.MCL.CS.COLUMBIA.EDU
                                "One Stop FTP"


 Welcome anonymous!

 The department of Computer of Science mirrors many sites on a nightly
 basis with many major Internet software packages.  A quick rundown
 includes: X11R[56], amd, gnu, emacs (and clones), Mosaic, Linux, RFCs,
 perl, rdist and whole lot more.  The README file in this directory
 contains our current exhaustive list.

 We may use your ID and host location info to generate usage stats.  We
 will make our results public from time to time.

 Your *transactions* are being logged at the request of several
 contributors who wish to maintain up-to-date records as to who has
 their software, so they can keep you up-to-date on changes, updates,
 and bug fixes as necessary.  Simple perusal commands (cd, ls, etc) are
 *not* logged.  If logging offends your, then please do not transfer
 from this site or close the connection now.

 Uploads are permissible to /incoming but only for temporary periods. 

 The server classifies accesses.
 You are connection number 2 out of a permitted 20.

 If you have questions about this site,  please mail ezk@ftp.cs.columbia.edu.

  You can:

  Strip .Z and .gz from archive names to get them uncompressed
  Add .gz or .Z to file names to get them compressed
  Add .tar, .tar.Z or .tar.gz to directory names to get them compressed
  Add .hqx to mac files to get them BinHex'ed
  Add .md5 to files to get their md5 sums.



 Guest login ok, access restrictions apply.

     If you don't like this policy, disconnect now!

     This is an experimental FTP server.
     If have any unusual problems, please report them via e-mail to
     root@localhost

     If you do have problems, please try using a dash  (-)  as  the
     first character  of  your password -- this will turn  off  the
     continuation  messages that may be confusing your ftp client.

  There are some extensions to the FTP server such that if you
  specify a filename (when using a RETRIEVE command) such that:
 
  True File  Specified File  Action
  ---------- -------------- ----------------------------------------
  'file'     'file'.Z        Compress     'file' before transmitting
  'file'.Z   'file'          Uncompress   'file' before transmitting
  'file'     'file'.gz       Gzip         'file' before transmitting
  'file'.gz  'file'          Ungzip       'file' before transmitting
  'file'     'file'.bz2      Bzip2        'file' before transmitting
  'file'.bz2 'file'          Unbzip2      'file' before transmitting
  'file'     'file'.tar      Tar          'file' before transmitting
  'file'     'file'.tar.Z    Tar+compress 'file' before transmitting
  'dir'      'dir'.tar.Z     Tar+compress 'dir'  before transmitting
  'file'     'file'.tar.gz   Tar+gzip     'file' before transmitting
  'dir'      'dir'.tar.gz    Tar+gzip     'dir'  before transmitting
  'file'     'file'.tar.bz2  Tar+bzip2    'file' before transmitting
  'dir'      'dir'.tar.bz2   Tar+bzip2    'dir'  before transmitting
 *******************************************************************

 *  Se ten problemas o conectar con este servidor de ftp anonimo probe a
 *  introducir unha contrasinal que comence polo caracter "-". Esto
 *  elimina as mensaxes de informacion, que poden confundir a alguns clientes
 *  de FTP
 *
 *  Os arquivos con extensions .gz ou .Z estan xa comprimidos
 *  Estes arquivos poden baixarse descomprimidos indicando o nome do
 *  arquivo sen a extension .gz ou .Z
 *  Pode baixarse comprimido un arquivo que non o estea no servidor indicando
 *  o nome do mesmo acabado en .gz ou .Z segun desexe que a compresion se
 *  efectue con gzip ou con compress de Unix
 *  Pode levarse directorios enteros especificando .tar o final do nome do
 *  directorio
 *

 dans le rpertoire 'incoming2' puis dans le rpertoire
 cach.

 Pour connatre le nom du rpertoire cach :

 - agents CEA, consultez l'URL http://www-dti.cea.fr:8000/services/ftp/ftp.htm,

 - autres, demandez  votre correspondant CEA le nom du rpertoire cach.

 Ce rpertoire cach ne permet pas la consultation de
 la liste des fichiers avec la commande 'ls'.

 Les fichiers vieux de 8 jours sont dtruits et votre
 session est journalise.
 ----------------------------------------------------------
 This server is only intended to allow exchanges between
 international community and CEA researchers.
 
 To store your files (< 300 Mo.), go to the 'incoming' directory
 then in the hidden directory.

 To store your big files (> 300 Mo.), go to the 'incoming2'
 directory then in the hidden directory.

 To know the name of this hidden directory :

 - CEA agents, consult the URL http://www-dti.cea.fr:8000/services/ftp/ftp.htm,

 - others, ask your CEA correspondent for the name of the hidden directory.

 This hidden directory is read protected, so it isn't possible
 to have the list of files with the 'ls' command.

 The files aged 8 days are deleted and your session is logged.
 -----------------------------------------------------------

                         -- IMPORTANT --

         * Tous les transferts sont enregistres pour permettre l'exploitation
         statistique de l'utilisation du serveur.
         * Les fichiers avec l'extension .gz sont compresses avec gzip et non
         avec compress.
         * Vous pouvez, si vous n'avez pas compress et gzip, decompresser "a la
         volee" (voir le document README.fly).

         * All transfers are logged with your host name and e-mail address
         to allow us to make statistics on the server use.
         * Files with a .gz extension are compressed with gzip.
         * You can also use the conversions mechanism when you want uncompress
         .Z and .gz files "on the fly" (see also the README.fly file)

 If your FTP client crashes or hangs shortly after login, try using a
 dash (-) as the first character of your password.  This will turn off
 the informational messages which may be confusing your ftp client.

 Note: this server supports file compression and decompression on the fly.
 You can download uncompressed files in compressed form (UNIX compress)
 by adding a .Z to the filename in a "get" command. Similarily, you can
 download compressed files in uncompressed form by specifying the filename
 without the trailing .Z.
 Using .gz or .bz2 instead of .Z is also possible, it simply means the use
 respectively of "gzip" or "bzip2" program instead of "compress".

 mailto:<info-ftp@infobiogen.fr>

============================== ftp://quatramaran.ens.fr/

       * Total file number: 145
       * Total file size: 7.30 MB
       * System: UNIX Type: L8
       * Directories in /pub/: ara/, cigaes/, espie/, fare/, madore/,
         misc/, mxk/, orabidoo/, sbi/
       * Welcome message:

 quatramaran.ens.fr FTP server (Version 6.5/OpenBSD, linux port 0.3.3) ready.
  This is the "quatramaran" ftp server on quatramaran.ens.fr.  Welcome.
 
  This site is maintained by a group of ENS students during their free time.
 
  In here, among other things, you'll find:
         ytalk, sirc, xtris                      in /pub/orabidoo
         bav3d, xplasma                          in /pub/mxk
         ftpd-BSD, unlambda, shsecret & more in /pub/madore
         flrn                                    in /pub/masse
         tbuffy                                  in /pub/quisar
         xglobe                                  in /pub/espie
 
  This site may be unexpectedly down for such ridiculous and futile reasons
  as: a hard disk breaking all of a sudden, someone stepping on the on/off
  switch, unexpected power failures, or a sysadmin going in a sudden
  reinstallation frenzy (all of these have happened at least once during the
  last year).  We apologize for the inconvenience.  Even when the site is
  not down, we have difficulties with our routers (from the Renater network)
  which sometimes render it inaccessible.
 
  We use ftpd-BSD-0.3.3, a Linux port formerly by David Madore of the OpenBSD
  ftp daemon.  You can find it in /pub/madore/ftpd-BSD/contrib/ on
  this site.
 
  In particular, this server handles on-the-fly uncompression of .gz files:
  if you see a .gz file, and you cannot uncompress it yourself, try to
  retrieve the same file without the .gz extension, and ftpd will uncompress
  it for you.  (But please try to avoid using this feature.  You can find
  a Windows version of gzip in /pub/misc/gzip.exe that will allow you to
  uncompress .gz files under MS-DOS or Windows.)
 
  Please contact ftp@quatramaran.ens.fr for questions and comments.
 Guest login ok, access restrictions apply.

 This is the FTP service for FTP.FNAL.GOV.

 The purpose of this service is to provide access to the
 following categories of files:
  - The FermiTools area: publicly available software under the
    /pub directory (all users).
  - The products area: This provides alternate access to files
    normally accessed via the upd program. (registered users)
  - The KITS area provides a backwards-compatable file tree for
    scripts, etc. used to the old upd directory layout.  It is NOT
    reccomended for browsing for files.

 This server allows for on-the-fly compression  and uncompression
 of files retrieved. It also allows you to tar up entire directory
 structures.


 You are NOT registered to retrieve files from the UNIX kits area.

 Retrieve the "registration" file if you want to become registered.
 The full path to the file is /registration.

 You MAY retrieve files from the FermiTools area under /pub. These
 files are available to the general public.

 Guest login ok, access restrictions apply.

 ftp.inel.gov FTP server ready.

 Updated Fri Feb 18 08:58:16 MST 2000

 NOTE:  The ls command seems to be broken, use DIR until further notice!

 General Information
   1. Users of the NT systems.
      Alot of people are using spaces in the names of their files when 
      saving files created from applications running on an NT server 
      or even a PC.  A Unix file system does not support spaces in file 
      names.  This can cause a retrieval to fail.
     
   2. Remember, files are purged after 14 days!

   3. Files compressed on this server are compressed using the GNU
      compress replacement, gzip.  gzipped files have the suffix .gz
      If you need gzip, down load ftp://ftp.inel.gov/pub/utils/gzip.tar 
      from this site!!!

 ready.
 Welcome to ftp.cs.cuhk.hk, the anonymous FTP Server of Department of
 Computer Science, The Chinese University of Hong Kong

 You are user 39 out of 100 allowed in your usage class.

 Access is allowed all day.
 All activity is logged with your host name and email address.

 For information on submitting software to this server, please retrieve
 /HOW_TO_SUBMIT.

 If your FTP client crashes or hangs shortly after login, try using a
 dash (-) as the first character of your password.  This will turn off
 the informational messages which may be confusing your ftp client.

 "get" <directory>.<suffix> or <file>.<suffix> where suffix comes from
 the set [gz, Z, tar, tar.Z, tar.gz] will compress and/or tar a file or
 directory for you on the fly.  Likewise if you strip suffixes from
 filenames, they can be uncompressed for you.

 ftp.cse.cuhk.edu.hk FTP server (Version wu-2.6.2(1) Tue Oct 15 17:22:07 HKT 2002)
 ready.
 Welcome to ftp.cs.cuhk.hk, the anonymous FTP Server of Department of
 Computer Science, The Chinese University of Hong Kong

 You are user 18 out of 100 allowed in your usage class.

 Access is allowed all day.
 All activity is logged with your host name and email address.

 For information on submitting software to this server, please retrieve
 /HOW_TO_SUBMIT.

 If your FTP client crashes or hangs shortly after login, try using a
 dash (-) as the first character of your password.  This will turn off
 the informational messages which may be confusing your ftp client.

 "get" <directory>.<suffix> or <file>.<suffix> where suffix comes from
 the set [gz, Z, tar, tar.Z, tar.gz] will compress and/or tar a file or
 directory for you on the fly.  Likewise if you strip suffixes from
 filenames, they can be uncompressed for you.

 Please send suggestions and questions to ftp@cs.cuhk.hk

 Please read the file README

 Compress/tar tricks:
    There are some extensions to the FTP server such that if the user
    specifies a filename (when using a RETRIEVE command) such that:

    True Filename   Used Filename     Action
    --------------  -------------     ---------------------------------------
    <filename>.gz   <filename>        De-gnuzip file before transmitting
    <filename>      <filename>.gz     Gnuzip file before transmitting
    <filename>      <filename>.tar    Tar file before transmitting
    <filename>      <filename>.tar.gz Tar and gnuzip file before transmitting

 aggiornate dei client per Internet oltre ad antivirus ed utilities varie. Se
 ti risulta piu' facile accedere tramite web, vai a questo indirizzo:

 http://www.eurolink.it/ftp-i.htm

 Per accedere all' area pubblica del nostro server FTP entra nella directory
 /pub. Se vuoi inviarci un file allora entra in /incoming. I file cosi'
 inviati verranno controllati e quindi spostati nell' area pubblica in modo
 da permettere l' accesso ad essi a tutti gli utenti della rete.

 Ricorda che molti programmi sono freeware, cioe' completamente gratuiti, ma
 altri sono shareware e richiedono una registrazione; per quanto riguarda i
 programmi shareware ti invitiamo a leggere le istruzioni incluse in ognuno
 di essi in quanto per ogni caso e' generalmente richiesto un procedimento di
 registrazione diverso.

 User ftp logged in.  Access restrictions apply.

   <filename>.gz  <filename>          Gunzip file before transmitting

   <filename>     <filename>.gz       gzip <filename> before transmitting
   <filename>     <filename>.tar      Tar <filename> before transmitting
   <filename>     <filename>.tar.Z    Tar and compress <filename> before
                                                 transmitting

 ********** SITE INDEX **********

  If you are using newer ftp client, you can find archive files
 by the command `site index filename'. Our `index' command
 supports many kinds of queries including arbitrary wild cards,
 sets of patterns, and in general, regular expressions. If you
 want to do a case-insensitive search, use `-i' option such as
 `site index -i filename'.
  (Also we accept `quote site {exec} index filename'.)

         Welcome to POSTECH archive from pD9E418EB.dip.t-dialin.net.
         You are 13-th user of 100 maximum in your class.
         20 local users and 50 remote users are allowed.
         Current time is Fri Aug 29 20:00:23 2003 KST.

          - ftpadm@ftp.postech.ac.kr

         [*** IMPORTANT NOTES ***]

         Since there were the evident abuses of /incoming
         directory, the policy of the /incoming directory
         has changed.

         Some ftp users put commerical softwares in /incoming
         for the illegal distribution of the softwares.
         (Shame on the creator of "plz_upload ***" stuffs!)
         We cleared out the whole /incoming directory, and
         restricted users from reading /incoming.

         Users outside POSTECH can only put files to the
         directory, not read the files. Users inside POSTECH
         can read the files via /afs/p/ftp/incoming directory.
         He must have HEMOS user account and login to AFS
         client in order to access the directory.

         For the HEMOS user accout requests, go to
                 http://www.postech.ac.kr/hemos

         ftp:/incoming is the place for the users outside
         POSTECH who can put files for POSTECH users. This
         should not be used for the illegal and intentional
         abusers.
                                 Since 1996,     HEMOS Admins.

 DrenikNet javni ftp server (ftp.drenik.net)

  -----------------------------------------------------------------
         Dobrodosli na najveci YU javni download server!
  -----------------------------------------------------------------

   Javni FTP servis DrenikNet-a smatra se najvecim javnim servisom
   u nasoj zemlji. Ovaj servis je dostupan svim korisnicima 24/7.
   Preporucujemo vam da posetite web servis ovog servera koji se
   nalazi na adresi: http://download.drenik.net/ jel mozete daleko
   lakse da pronadjete ono sto vam je potrebno. Za svaki download
   savetujemo vam da koristite neki od download menadzera ili bilo
   koji software koji ima mogucnost nastavka download procesa.

   Ukoliko zelite da kontaktirate DrenikNet : office@drenik.net
   Ukoliko zelite da prijavite zloupotrebu  : abuse@drenik.net

   System Administrator : Luka Gerzic < stinger@drenik.net >

     DrenikNet download team vam zeli brz download i dobru vezu!

============================== ftp://ftp.pdp8.net/

       * Total file number: 88
       * Total file size: 17.94 MB
       * System: UNIX Type: L8
       * Welcome message:

 hugin.sabir.com FTP server (Version wu-2.6.2-5) ready.
 PDP8 file archive. 
 For anonymous if you want to upload a file for me use /images/incoming.  Please
 send me email saying what you have uploaded.

 You can compress files on the fly by adding the extension for the
 type of compression you want (.Z, .gz, .zip).  If you use .zip, or .tar.gz or
 .tgz on a directory it will pack up and compress the entire directory.

 Example to get file edu30.tu56  gzipped use get edu30.tu56.gz.

 If you are using netscape you will need to use something like
 ftp://ftp.pdp8.net/images/os8/edu30.tu56.zip
 ftp://ftp.pdp8.net/images/paper_tape.zip

 This site is connected by a 128kbit upstream DSL modem.  Please don't try to
 transfer more that one file at a time and transfer compressed like above
 if getting lots of stuff.

 Take a look at my website at http://www.pdp8.net/

 Software is copyrighted, much not for commercial use.  See COPYRIGHT.TXT
 David Gesswein djg@pdp8.net

 This server understands REGET, MDTM and all other nifty stuff.  You can
 get any file in compressed form by adding .Z to the filename (gzipped: .gz,
 frozen: .F), directories by adding .tar to the directory name.  Compression
 accelerates transfers if your connection is slower than 20 KByte/s.
 Vice-versa, you need not install gzip/freeze at home: simply omit the
 suffix .Z, .gz or .F when getting a file.

 ######################################################################
 Welcome to your FTP server!

 Root login via FTP is disallowed by default. Please use an SFTP client
 (or other secure protocol such as SSH) to connect as root for file
 transfers.

 If you are in a country that does not allow strong encryption or have
 other problems connecting via a secure protocol, you may enable FTP
 logins for root by adding the following line to /etc/proftpd.conf
 file:

     RootLogin on

 Logging in to your server via non-secure protocols such as FTP is
 considered dangerous because potential snoopers on your network may
 be eavesdropping and obtain your account password, giving them full
 control of the compromised account.
 ######################################################################

 PLEASE NOTE:

 All Public files are located in the /pub folder.

 If you are a VIA NET.WORKS customer, you can upload files into the /local
 folder. To do this, log in with:

 User ID: anonymous
 Password: your e-mail address

 Note that you cannot create sub-folders in /local. You can download
 files from any part of this FTP site.

 If you are an FTP user who is not a VIA NET.WORKS customer, you can only
 upload files into the /remote folder. You cannot download files from
 the /remote folder, but you can download files from any other part of
 this FTP site.


 For help please email support@vianetworks.co.uk

     This is the FTP server at the  Department of Computer Science,
  Utrecht University, the Netherlands (Europe).

    get DIR.zip         get FIL.gz
    get DIR.tar.gz
    get DIR.tgz         # NOTE : don't use absolute path-names,
    get DIR.tar.bz2     # that is, names that start with a '/'

  as any unusual problems you might encounter while using this service,
  may be e-mailed to: <archivist@cs.uu.nl>

   *                                                             *
   *  In case you don't know what everything means, here are     *
   *  some hints:                                                *
   *  - files ending in .Z are compressed using the Unix         *
   *    command 'compress'.                                      *
   *  - files ending in .gz or .zip are compressed using 'gzip'  *
   *    and be uncompressed using the widely available gzip.     *
   *  - files containging .tar are archives build by the Unix    *
   *    command 'tar'.                                           *
   *  - files containing .ps contain PostScript typesetting code *
   *  - files containing .tex contain TeX typesetting code       *
   *  - files ending in .tif are TIFF encoded pictures .         *
   *  - files ending in .c contain C-language program code       *
   *  - files ending in .f contain Fortran program code.         *
   *  - files ending in .hqx are 7-bit encoded Macintosh files   *
   *  - files ending in .txt are (ASCII) tekst files             *
   *                                                             *
   ***************************************************************

 oosix.icce.rug.nl FTP server ready.

     -----------------------------------------------------------------------
     This is the main-README file of the anonymous ftp-site ftp.icce.rug.nl.
     -----------------------------------------------------------------------

 The only place where you'll find useful information around here is located
 under the 'pub' subdirectory. This includes our 'incoming' directories as
 well.

 ANONYMOUS USERS OF ftp.icce.rug.nl ARE ONLY ALLLOWED TO RETRIEVE INFORMATION
 FROM THE DIRECTORIES UNDER 
                               /pub and /infozip
 ANONYMOUS USERS OF ftp.icce.rug.nl ARE ALLOWED TO UPLOAD FILES TO THE
 /pub/incoming/<username> DIRECTORIES.

 ATTEMPTS TO CREATE SUBDIRECTORIES, OR TO USE THE CHMOD COMMAND IS NOT ALLOWED
 AND ARE INTERPRETED AS DELIBERATE ATTEMPTS TO ABUSE THIS SITE FOR ILLEGAL
 PURPOSES.

 OUR REACTION TO SUCH ATTEMPTS IS TO DENY FURTHER ACCESS TO ftp.icce.rug.nl
 FROM YOUR ADDRESS.

 All transfers and commands issued by anonymous ftp users are actively
 monitored. If you don't like this policy, logout now.

         Frank Brokken (f.b.brokken@rc.rug.nl)

 If you do have problems, please try using a dash (-) as the first character of
 your password -- this will turn off the continuation messages that may be
 confusing your ftp client.

                                "One Stop FTP"


 Welcome anonymous!

 The department of Computer of Science mirrors many sites on a nightly
 basis with many major Internet software packages.  A quick rundown
 includes: X11R[56], amd, gnu, emacs (and clones), Mosaic, Linux, RFCs,
 perl, rdist and whole lot more.  The README file in this directory
 contains our current exhaustive list.

 We may use your ID and host location info to generate usage stats.  We
 will make our results public from time to time.

 Your *transactions* are being logged at the request of several
 contributors who wish to maintain up-to-date records as to who has
 their software, so they can keep you up-to-date on changes, updates,
 and bug fixes as necessary.  Simple perusal commands (cd, ls, etc) are
 *not* logged.  If logging offends your, then please do not transfer
 from this site or close the connection now.

 Uploads are permissible to /incoming but only for temporary periods. 

 The server classifies accesses.
 You are connection number 3 out of a permitted 20.

 If you have questions about this site,  please mail ezk@ftp.cs.columbia.edu.

 *******************************************************

 Hallo!

 Das ist einer der offiziellen Debian Mirrors in Oesterreich.

 Hier wird debian und debian-non-US gefuehrt.

 Weiters gibt es die offiziellen ISO Images, um Debian von CD
 installieren zu koennen.
 Fuer naehere Informationen, wie man am besten an die ISO Images
 rankommt, so lese man bitte naeheres auf http://www.at.debian.org/CD/
 nach, im speziellen ueber das Pseudo Image Kit.
 Aber sie sind auch ueber rsync von diesem Server zu beziehen.

 Weiters sind noch folgende Module fuer rsync verfuegbar:
 debian-web, debian-ftp, wwwgnu und ftpgnu.

 Have fun!
 Othmar Pasteka, mirror@atnet.at

 ********** SITE INDEX **********

  If you are using newer ftp client, you can find archive files
 by the command `site index filename'. Our `index' command
 supports many kinds of queries including arbitrary wild cards,
 sets of patterns, and in general, regular expressions. If you
 want to do a case-insensitive search, use `-i' option such as
 `site index -i filename'.
  (Also we accept `quote site {exec} index filename'.)

 ftp.tex.ac.uk FTP server (Version wu-2.6.1(2) Fri Nov 30 09:35:16 GMT 2001) ready.
 Welcome to the University of Cambridge Computer Laboratory FTP server

 Problems should be reported to maintain@cl.cam.ac.uk.

 Welcome, archive user!

 This is an FTP server for the UK TeX Archive.  If you have any unusual
 problems, please report them via e-mail to ctan@ftp.tex.ac.uk.  If you
 do have problems, please try using a dash (-) as the first character
 of your password -- this will turn off the continuation messages that
 may be confusing your ftp client.

 This is the UK node of the Comprehensive TeX Archive Network (CTAN).
 The other participating hosts in the CTAN and their root CTAN
 directories are:
         ftp.dante.de            tex-archive
         ctan.tug.org            tex-archive
 In order to reduce network load, it is recommended that you use
 the CTAN host which is located in the closest proximity to your
 site.  The file CTAN.sites lists known mirrors of CTAN.

 IMPORTANT NOTE:

 This ftp server supports dynamic creation of zip, zoo, or tar.gz
 archives.  If you want the contents of a directory (*and all its
 subdirectories*), go to the level above and `get' the directory name
 suffixed by .zip, zoo or .tar.gz e.g.

    cd /pub/archive/macros/latex/contrib/supported
    binary
    get rotating.zip

 will put together the whole "rotating" package for you.

 Guest login ok, access restrictions apply.

 Welcome to the Caca Volante FTP Site.

 If you have experienced trouble logging in in the past, it may
 just mean the site was full.  For best results, I suggest that
 you access the site using an FTP client such as CuteFTP or
 BulletProof FTP rather than your web browser.

 Uploads are very appreciated (though not required), but please
 make sure you aren't uploading something that is already under
 /pub somewhere, and please no full albums that can be purchased
 legitimately -- I will not make those available for download.
 You may upload and create folders in the /incoming directory.
 I would appreciate audio at 192kbps or better, but I'm not too
 picky. 

 If you upload any Mr. Bungle, Fantmas, or Mike Patton solo
 projects, the files will be transferred to ftp.bunglefever.com
 for download there.

 Problems, questions, requests, or PayPal donations can be sent
 to andy@cv.org.

 Thanks for your support and enjoy!

 Mobile Computing Lab, FTP maintainers <ftp@shekel.mcl.cs.columbia.edu>
 Columbia University Department of Computer Science.

 shekel.mcl.cs.columbia.edu FTP server (Version wu-2.6.0(3) Tue Oct 19 18:30:07 EDT
 1999) ready.
                      WELCOME TO FTP.MCL.CS.COLUMBIA.EDU
                                "One Stop FTP"


 Welcome anonymous!

 The department of Computer of Science mirrors many sites on a nightly
 basis with many major Internet software packages.  A quick rundown
 includes: X11R[56], amd, gnu, emacs (and clones), Mosaic, Linux, RFCs,
 perl, rdist and whole lot more.  The README file in this directory
 contains our current exhaustive list.

 We may use your ID and host location info to generate usage stats.  We
 will make our results public from time to time.

 Your *transactions* are being logged at the request of several
 contributors who wish to maintain up-to-date records as to who has
 their software, so they can keep you up-to-date on changes, updates,
 and bug fixes as necessary.  Simple perusal commands (cd, ls, etc) are
 *not* logged.  If logging offends your, then please do not transfer
 from this site or close the connection now.

 Uploads are permissible to /incoming but only for temporary periods. 

 The server classifies accesses.
 You are connection number 2 out of a permitted 20.

 If you have questions about this site,  please mail ezk@ftp.cs.columbia.edu.

 www.hylafax.org FTP server (Version wu-2.6.0(1) Fri Jun 23 09:21:17 EDT 2000) ready.

         Welcome to the HylaFAX(tm) FTP repository. HylaFAX is a
         full-featured, extensible and freely available facsimile
         solution for UNIX systems.

         The following sub-directories are present here:

 source          HylaFAX *source code* distributions and related binary packages
 binary          HylaFAX binary distributions
 archives        archives of the FlexFAX/HylaFAX mailing list. For a proper
                 view of these archives, and other mailing list info, see
                        
                         http://www.hylafax.org/mailing-lists.html

 bakeoff         the "FlexFAX Modem Bakeoff" paper; this is also available via
                 the WWW at

                     http://www.hylafax.org/Bakeoff/paper.html

 contrib         contributed software for use with HylaFAX
 incoming        place where HylaFAX users can leave things for the
                 contrib area (note that this directory is scrubbed nightly
                 so if you don't notify me that something's there, it'll
                 get removed)

 If you don't know what you want, fetch the file HOWTO in this directory
 and read it before proceeding any further.

 There is a mass of HylaFAX information available through the WWW

                         http://www.hylafax.org/

 If you can't find answers to your questions, send a detailed message to
 hylafax-users@hylafax.org.

         Darren Nickerson <darren@hylafax.org>

 ********** SITE INDEX **********

  If you are using newer ftp client, you can find archive files
 by the command `site index filename'. Our `index' command
 supports many kinds of queries including arbitrary wild cards,
 sets of patterns, and in general, regular expressions. If you
 want to do a case-insensitive search, use `-i' option such as
 `site index -i filename'.

 sicher nichts.

 Was auch immer hier abgeht, es wird beobachtet, um unzulaessige Zugriffe
 und Angriffe auf das System zu erkennen. Im Zuge dieser Beobachtung
 gewonnene Kenntnisse koennen sich morgen schon in der Bildzeitung oder
 bei der zustaendigen Staatsanwaltschaft wiederfinden.

 Wer mit dieser Beobachtung nicht einverstanden ist, sollte das System
 jetzt wieder verlassen.

 Es macht uebrigens keinen Sinn, hier html, pl, cgi, php, asp oder
 aehnliche Dateien hochzuladen. Auf das allgemeine Upload-Verzeichnis
 kann natuerlich vom Webserver aus nicht zugegriffen werden.

============================== ftp://ftp.openpkg.org/

       * Total file number: 13,289
       * Total file size: 14.06 GB
       * System: UNIX Type: L8

       * Welcome message:

 ftp.openpkg.org OpenPKG Anonymous FTP Server (ProFTPD) ready.
    ___                   ____  _  ______
   / _ \ _ __   ___ _ __ |  _ \| |/ / ___|     The world of
  | | | | '_ \ / _ \ '_ \| |_) | ' / |  _      cross-platform
  | |_| | |_) |  __/ | | |  __/| . \ |_| |     RPM-based Unix
   \___/| .__/ \___|_| |_|_|   |_|\_\____|.org software packaging
  _____ |_| _____________________________________________________

  A flexible and powerful software packaging facility, OpenPKG
  eases installation and administration of Unix software across
  several platforms. It primarily targets the Unix platforms
  FreeBSD, Linux and Solaris, but is portable across mostly all
  modern Unix flavors. Consolidating different vendor approaches
  into a unified architecture, it assists in administration of
  large networks previously complicated by nonconformant systems.

  OpenPKG leverages proven technologies like Red Hat Package
  Manager (RPM) and neatly provides an additional system layer
  on top of the operating system. It is a fully self-contained
  with minimal external dependencies (no RPM pre-installation
  required), and installs itself by means of a tricky
  bootstrapping procedure with minimal operating system intrusion.
  OpenPKG especially supports multiple installation instances on
  the same system.
 
  For more details visit http://www.openpkg.org/

  Distribution Master Location:
    ftp://ftp.openpkg.org/ .......................... C&W, DE
  Distribution Mirror Locations:
    ftp://ftp.de.cw.net/pub/openpkg/ ................ C&W, DE
    ftp://rpmfind.net/linux/OpenPKG/ ................ MIT, US
    ftp://ftp.rpmfind.net/linux/OpenPKG/ ...... Speakeasy, US
    ftp://at.rpmfind.net/linux/OpenPKG/ ....... TU Vienna, AT
    ftp://fr.rpmfind.net/linux/OpenPKG/ ........... INRIA, FR
    ftp://fr2.rpmfind.net/linux/OpenPKG/ ........... INSA, FR
    ftp://ftp.icm.edu.pl/site/openpkg/ .............. ICM, PL
    ftp://ftp.ntua.gr/pub/linux/openpkg/ ........... NTUA, GR
    ftp://sunsite.icm.edu.pl/pub/linux/openpkg/ ..... ICM, PL

 This server understands REGET, MDTM and all other nifty stuff.  You can
 get any file in compressed form by adding .Z to the filename (gzipped: .gz,
 frozen: .F), directories by adding .tar to the directory name.  Compression
 accelerates transfers if your connection is slower than 20 KByte/s.
 Vice-versa, you need not install gzip/freeze at home: simply omit the
 suffix .Z, .gz or .F when getting a file.

============================== ftp://ftp.rcsb.org/

       * Total file number: 179,472
       * Total file size: 16.19 GB
       * System: UNIX Type: L8
       * Directories in /pub/: pdb/
       * Welcome message:

 =======================================================================
             
           **  Welcome to the PDB ANONYMOUS FTP account **
  
 This FTP site provides access to data on the 3-D structure of biological
 macromolecules.

 It is strongly recommended to use the uniformly-formatted mmCIF files,
 with standardized nomenclature and matched SEQRES-coordinate sequences,
 which can be accessed at

 ftp://beta.rcsb.org/pub/pdb/uniformity/data/mmCIF/. 

 Details about these files can be found at
 http://www.rcsb.org/pdb/uniformity/index.html .

 This account is maintained by the Research Collaboratory for
 Structural Bioinformatics (RCSB; http://www.rcsb.org). If you have any
 questions about this archive please send email to info@rcsb.org.

 Structure data is located in pub/pdb/data/structures.

 Entry files are date-stamped to show the date they were released.

 Note: Users should switch to binary mode before downloading data files.
 =======================================================================
 Entry Directory Layout:

   data/status/yyyymmdd/update.ls-lR
  
       * contains ls-lR listing of added, modified and obsolete entries
         for that week.

   data/structures/divided/pdb/nn/*

       * is originally last quarterly full release BUT then is modified
         to include withdrawn (removed), replacement, and additional
         entries since last quarterly full release

       * is the current full release (last quarterly plus updates)

       * divided into 2-letter directories

   data/structures/divided/mmCIF/nn/*
   data/structures/divided/nmr_restraints/nn/*
   data/structures/divided/structure_factors/nn/*

       * analogous to the divided/pdb directory, containing
         mmCIF, nmr restraint, and structure factor files, respectively.

   data/structures/all/*

       * analogous to the divided directory, containing pdb,
         mmCIF, nmr_restraint, and structure_factors directories,
         with symbolic links to files in the divided subdirectories.
         These are not divided into two-letter directories

   data/structures/obsolete/pdb/nn/*
   data/structures/obsolete/mmCIF/nn/*
   data/structures/obsolete/nmr_restraints/nn/*
   data/structures/obsolete/structure_factors/nn/*

       * analogous to the divided directories, but containing
         obsolete files.

 =======================================================================
 Help File Descriptions:

   ls-lR             full listing of all files in FTP

   ftphelp.txt       instructions for using FTP

   how2dnld.txt      instructions on how to download a file     

 To get one of these files, type "get filename" then logout to view it
 on your local system.
 =======================================================================

 This is the ../pdb directory of the RCSB PDB ftp archive.

 Directories available from this level are:

 derived_data/   Information derived from PDB files
 xternal/        Any external information related to the PDB
 software/       Software provided by the PDB
 doc/            Documentation
 data/           Atomic coordinates, experimental information,
                 HET dictionary and information on monomers
        
 =================================================================
 This account is maintained by the Research Collaboratory for
 Structural Bioinformatics (RCSB; http://www.rcsb.org).

 If you have any questions about this archive please send email to
 info@rcsb.org.
 =======================================================================
 If you can't scroll backwards to view this file, get it by typing
 "get README" then logout to view it on your local system.
 =======================================================================

 ftp2.rcsb.org FTP server ready.
 =======================================================================
             
           **  Welcome to the PDB ANONYMOUS FTP account **

 This FTP site provides access to data on the 3-D structure of biological
 macromolecules.

 It is strongly recommended to use the uniformly-formatted mmCIF files,
 with standardized nomenclature and matched SEQRES-coordinate sequences,
 which can be accessed at

 ftp://beta.rcsb.org/pub/pdb/uniformity/data/mmCIF/. 

 Details about these files can be found at
 http://www.rcsb.org/pdb/uniformity/index.html .
  
 This account is maintained by the Research Collaboratory for
 Structural Bioinformatics (RCSB; http://www.rcsb.org). If you have any
 questions about this archive please send email to info@rcsb.org.

 Structure data is located in pub/pdb/data/structures.

 Entry files are date-stamped to show the date they were released.

 Note: Users should switch to binary mode before downloading data files.
 =======================================================================

 be built outside of the United States of America or Canada for the use of

 on that mechanism.

 Welcome anonymous user from 217.228.24.235 ...

   You have connected to the Use Linux FTP Server.
   This server is maintained by: mirrors@uselinux.org

   Currently, 7 user(s) out of 350 maximum are connected.

   All connections and transfers are being logged. 

 -------------------------------------------------------------------
  This is a dual AMD 1.2GHz system with 2GB RAM, and roughly 220GB
  of storage (RAID 1+0).  Network connectivity is handled via
  dual 1000Mbit full-duplex switched ethernet, which feeds from
  a Cisco backbone switch that traverses fiber into a multi-homed
  ATM network. 

  Major NAPS providing upstream bandwidth include UUnet, Level3,
  Cable & Wireless, and SprintLink.

  A HUGE thanks to Andrew Lindh and NETPLEX Internet Services for
  providing server co-location space, power, etc. and tremendous
  amounts of bandwidth.  They have been sponsoring and helping
  to support this server since 1996.
 
  Be sure to visit their website at >>> http://www.netplex.net/ <<<
  to see what they can do for you or your company.  You can also
  send a nice thank you to support@ntplx.net if you use and
  appreciate these services.

  Visit http://uselinux.org/ for more information about who
  we are and what we're mirroring.

 Available RETRIEVE (GET) command extensions (use binary transfers):

 True Filename Specified Filename               Action
 -------------- ------------------ ---------------------------------------
 <filename>    <filename>.Z       compress <filename> before sending
 <filename>    <filename>.gz      gzip <filename> before sending

 Laboratory (cl.cam.ac.uk)

 ftp host=ftp.cl.cam.ac.uk login=ftp                 pw=your-email-address
 WWW http://www.ftp.cl.cam.ac.uk/ftp or http://www.ftp.cl.cam.ac.uk/ftp/home.html

 contacted if you have problems, the file is found to be out of date, etc),

 balblair FTP server (Version wu-2.6.2(1) Mon Dec 3 13:03:36 GMT 2001) ready.

 The directory 'incoming' and 'incoming.secure' have been removed
 from this server.  If you need to upload scientific files to the
 MRC Human Genetics Unit you will now need to use,

        ftp://ftpin.hgu.mrc.ac.uk/incoming

 You may also need to contact the FTP Server Maintainer
 to give you access,

        mailto: ftp@hgu.mrc.ac.uk

 Compressed files on this server can be pulled in  their  original
 form  by  dropping  the  .Z  or  .gz extension; ie use 'get file'
 rather than 'get file.Z'.

 Alternatively, files can be tar'd and/or compressed when  pulling
 by  specifying  'file.tar',  'file.tar.Z'  or  'file.tar.gz' etc,
 rather than the filename 'file'.   This  option  is  useful  when
 pulling a directory.

       * Welcome message:

 pisces.shef.ac.uk FTP server (Version wu-2.6.2(1) Mon Dec 3 09:50:06 GMT 2001)
 ready.
 Welcome anonymous from pD9E418EB.dip.t-dialin.net.

 This is the University of Sheffield's anonymous FTP server.

 This server is maintained by ftpadmin@shef.ac.uk.

 It available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.

 The local time is Fri Aug 29 12:07:05 2003 and you are user 11 out
 of a maximum of 50.

 All accesses to this server are logged --- if you don't like this policy,
 disconnect now!

 Most of the files on this server are compressed using the GNU compress
 replacement, gzip:  gzipped files have the suffix .gz

 If you can't uncompress gzipped files, you can have them uncompressed by the
 server before transmission by giving the file name WITHOUT the .gz suffix to
 the 'get' command.

 For instance, if the file is called DESCRIPTIONS.gz, you can get an uncompressed
 version by typing

         get DESCRIPTIONS

 It is also possible to tar directories on the fly -- if the directory is called
 lots-of-little-files/ then to get a tarred copy of the directory type

         get lots-of-little-files.tar

 You can also get it tarred and compressed with the command

         get lots-of-little-files.tar.gz

 Guest login ok, access restrictions apply.
